# StudyOS Accessibility Standards

## Accessibility Vision

StudyOS is committed to creating an inclusive learning environment that serves all users, regardless of their abilities, technologies, or circumstances. Our accessibility implementation follows the principle of Universal Design - creating products that are usable by all people, to the greatest extent possible, without the need for adaptation.

## WCAG 2.1 AA Compliance Framework

### The Four Principles (POUR)

#### 1. Perceivable
Information and user interface components must be presentable to users in ways they can perceive.

#### 2. Operable  
User interface components and navigation must be operable by all users.

#### 3. Understandable
Information and the operation of user interface must be understandable.

#### 4. Robust
Content must be robust enough that it can be interpreted reliably by a wide variety of user agents, including assistive technologies.

